FZF CHEATSHEET

USAGE: fzf [options]
       Fuzzy finder for command-line

BASIC COMMANDS:
  fzf                         Interactive fuzzy finder
  command | fzf               Pipe output to fzf
  fzf --query="pattern"       Start with search pattern
  fzf --multi                 Enable multi-selection

DEFAULT KEY BINDINGS:
  CTRL-T                      File search with preview
  CTRL-R                      Command history search
  OPT-C                       Directory navigation

NAVIGATION:
  ↑/↓ or CTRL-J/K            Move cursor up/down
  CTRL-U                      Preview page up
  CTRL-D                      Preview page down
  Enter                       Select item
  Tab                         Multi-select/deselect
  OPT-Enter                   Select all + accept (Only --multi)

SEARCH & FILTER:
  Type                        Start searching
  CTRL-/                      Toggle search mode
  CTRL-S                      Toggle sort

PREVIEW WINDOW:
  CTRL-F                      Toggle preview on/off
  CTRL-E                      Change preview position (down/hidden)

SPECIAL ACTIONS:
  CTRL-R (in file mode)       Reload file list
  CTRL-O (in file mode)       Open file in editor
  CTRL-Y (in history)         Copy command to clipboard
  ESC                         Cancel/exit

CUSTOM FUNCTIONS:
  fze [pattern]               Find and edit files
                             - Multi-select with Tab
                             - Open directly with CTRL-O

FILE SEARCH (CTRL-T):
  Enter                       Select file(s)
  Tab                         Toggle multi-selection
  CTRL-O                      Open in nvim
  CTRL-F                      Toggle preview

HISTORY SEARCH (CTRL-R):
  Enter                       Execute command
  CTRL-Y                      Copy to clipboard
  CTRL-F                      Toggle preview

DIRECTORY NAVIGATION (OPT-C):
  Enter                       Change to directory
  CTRL-F                      Toggle preview

